100% works, though files are CBR files. You need a special program to use them, though I think you can convert the files into ZIP or RAR files and extract the individual pages out of the file but it is easier to just download a program to open and view the comics. 

Thank you for the upload, thank you a whole bunch.

Thanks a lot man.

Brazilian editions of Star Wars comics are rare and incomplete, and many stories from different periods in time are condensed in a single monthly volume with low-quality paper.

You uploaders guys are real life-savers! I've already got this one and strongly recommend it!
thanks dude this should keep me happy for the time being
Thanks so much for this! I'll seed indefinitely.
